Julia played tag with 16 kids on monday. If she played tag with 12 more kids on monday than on tuesday How many kids did she play with on tuesday? 

Let x be the number of kids Julia played with on tuesday. Then, we have the following two equations:

\begin{aligned} 16 &= x + 12 \\ x &= 16 - 12 \end{aligned}

from the first equation, we get:

\begin{aligned} x + 12 &= 16 \\ x &= 14 \end{aligned}

from the second equation, we get:

\begin{aligned} x &= 16 - 12 = 4 \end{aligned}

So, Julia played with 4 kids on tuesday.
